  "name": "Wan 2.2 Bernini-R — AI image editing",
  "description": "Edit an image by describing the change in words. Upload an image and type an instruction (e.g. \"make it night\", \"add snow\", \"turn the car red\") — the Bernini-R model (Wan 2.2) regenerates the image following your prompt while keeping the composition.\n\n• **Edit type** steers the model — \"Image Editing\" for normal edits; \"Default\" is a more neutral prompt.\n• **Fast mode** (Turbo LoRA) is on by default — ~6 steps, quick and light. Turn it off for slower, higher-quality 40-step runs.\n\nFor editing guided by a second (reference) image, use the \"with reference\" version instead.",
